cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for semantic segmentation of shapes based on user-prescribed tags. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of tags for segmentation also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions testing on segmentation benchmarks (cs.GR), further supporting the likelihood of these sub-categories.
